Please replace this simp call with the output of `simp? [Monic]`. That is more robust.
(This is called "squeezing the simp".)

Non-squeezed simps are "flexible" tactics, and they can only be followed by other flexible tactics.
It feels like we should have `IsIntegral.of_neg` / `isIntegral_neg_iff`
